<h4>
    Angular Displacement
</h4>

<p>
    When we first learned about kinematics,
    we learned about both position and displacement.
    Position represents where you are,
    and displacement represents your change in position.
    Angular position and displacement work similarly,
    but with some complications.
</p>

<ul class = 'definition' data-word = 'Angular Displacement'>
    <li>
        Angular displacement represents change in angular position.
        It represents how much and object spins.
    </li>
    <li>
        Even though angular position cannot be greater than \( 2 \pi \),
        angular displacement <em>can</em>, if an object completes more
        than one rotation.
    </li>
    <li>
        Even though angular position is never negative,
        angular displacement <em>can be</em>.
        Positive angular displacement represents an object moving
        clockwise and negative angular displacement
        represents an object moving counterclockwise.
    </li>
    <li>
        The symbol for angular displacement is Delta-Theta: \( \Delta \theta \).
    </li>
</ul>

